,0.17892317,-0.05326736,0.02736017,-0.00749263,0.02180959,-0.03959600,0.06179873,0.05185493,0.00824762,0.01298393,0.11039449,0.05737885,0.02459792,0.01564108,0.04763872,-0.02092644,0.02487873,-0.00646342,0.04257959,0.01345398,-0.05612497,-0.00622867,-0.01670603,0.07226958,0.04214577,0.04553054,-0.08667061,0.04124239,-0.03317179,-0.01048007,0.01053063,-0.02261175,0.05427025,0.04831987,-0.06618454,0.02478754,0.02701107,-0.00634441,0.03209386,-0.04705551,-0.01057303,0.05918125,-0.02368763]',E'Embeddings Model API\n\n* *Simplicity*: EmbeddingModel simplifies the process of converting text to embeddings.\nBy providing straightforward methods like `embed(String text)` and `embed(Document document)`, it takes the complexity out of dealing with raw text data and embedding algorithms. This design choice makes it easier for developers, especially those new to AI, to utilize embeddings in their applications without delving deep into the underlying mechanics.','{"source": "spring-ai", "version": "1.0", "language": "java", "title": "Embeddings.Adoc", "section_title": "embeddings.adoc", "url": "https://github.com/spring-projects/spring-ai/blob/main/spring-ai-docs/src/main/antora/modules/ROOT/pages/api/embeddings.adoc", "topics": "spring,ai,llm,embeddings.adoc", "categories": "ai,java,llm,embeddings"}');
