0,0.16942941,0.01269215,0.02856561,0.00762519,-0.00045507,-0.05941237,0.04472014,-0.01789084,0.01401175,0.00967887,0.08472893,0.03065123,0.08087976,-0.02206372,0.05201885,-0.03013967,0.01031818,0.01421301,0.03484135,-0.00201491,-0.05514169,0.00894669,-0.01235502,0.06784912,-0.00111099,0.02585636,-0.06501467,0.01517058,0.03738980,-0.12498116,-0.03509799,-0.03004416,0.06112200,0.05388913,-0.02089901,0.03113842,-0.04760191,0.04366516,0.08671635,-0.03363779,-0.01539647,0.04921056,-0.03427573]',E'API Overview\n\nThe Embedding Model API is built on top of the generic https://github.com/spring-projects/spring-ai/tree/main/spring-ai-model/src/main/java/org/springframework/ai/model[Spring AI Model API], which is a part of the Spring AI library.\nAs such, the EmbeddingModel interface extends the `Model` interface, which provides a standard set of methods for interacting with AI models. The `EmbeddingRequest` and `EmbeddingResponse` classes extend from the `ModelRequest` and `ModelResponse` are used to encapsulate the input and output of the embedding models, respectively.\n\nThe Embedding API in turn is used by higher-level components to implement Embedding Models for specific embedding models, such as OpenAI, Titan, Ollie, and others.\n\nFollowing diagram illustrates the Embedding API and its relationship with the Spring AI Model API and the Embedding Models:\n\nimage:embeddings-api.jpg[title=Embeddings API,align=center,width=900]','{"source": "spring-ai", "version": "1.0", "language": "java", "title": "Embeddings.Adoc", "section_title": "embeddings.adoc", "url": "https://github.com/spring-projects/spring-ai/blob/main/spring-ai-docs/src/main/antora/modules/ROOT/pages/api/embeddings.adoc", "topics": "spring,ai,llm,embeddings.adoc", "categories": "ai,java,llm,embeddings"}');
